d of \\\"different or unknown,\\\" which may have changed. I need to ensure that logback-core and logback-classic versions are checked for warnings. If they're the same (1.5.26), that's good.\\n\\nI’ll implement two tests in a dedicated file and think about how ContextInitializerTest fits. Using MethodHandle.invoke might throw Throwable, so a multi-catch could be necessary. Plus, I should consider potential issues with reflection metadata, especially since the private methods may not be correctly analyzed in a native image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring MethodHandles and Native Image**\\n\\nI’m considering how MethodHandles might avoid configuration since they aren’t reflection-based. But with a Native Image, reflection configuration could be needed for method handles. MethodHandles.Lookup.findVirtual performs dynamic lookups based on strings at runtime, so does Native Image support them?\\n\\nIt appears MethodHandles and reflection are separate metadata, suggesting that the target must be accessible and discoverable. I’m uncertain if GraalVM handles this well. There’s also the possibility of private methods being included or not marked as reachable, which could lead to build failing or runtime errors.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method access risks**\\n\\nI'm realizing that direct reflection requires metadata for private methods, which I can't access since it’s absent in native. Annotations for testing aren't an option either. I could try using `ContextInitializer.class.getDeclaredMethod` and set it accessible, but that wouldn't work either. Relying solely on public APIs seems safer, but would lack coverage.\\n\\nI wondered about using a subclass in the same package, but that’s not allowed. I’m even considering `sun.misc.Unsafe`, but I'll need the method offset, which seems impossible too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering bytecode manipulation**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the possibility of manipulating bytecode, but it seems like we don't have any source stubs available. With the need for thorough task coverage, I’ll likely use MethodHandles for this. I need to check all the imports to ensure everything is in order. Also, should I avoid broadening by editing existing tests? It might be better to create a new file instead. Let’s see where this leads!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KVSVlBga4VS64C4ffPjQn0DQ|fc_0dc4787d6aa6fc64016a057b80e8f881a3b53257697e5afd96", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/src/test/java/org/graalvm/logback/ContextInitializerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org.graalvm.logback;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.Logger;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.Configurator;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.ILoggingEvent;\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.util.ContextInitializer;\nimport ch.qos.logback.core.Appender;\nimport ch.qos.logback.core.status.Status;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ContextInitializerTest {\n\n  @Test\n  void autoConfigReportsMatchingSelfDeclaredVersions() throws Exception {\n    LoggerContext loggerContext = new LoggerContext();\n    try {\n      ContextInitializer initializer = new ContextInitializer(loggerContext);\n      initializer.autoConfig(ContextInitializerTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n      List<Status> statuses = loggerContext.getStatusManager().getCopyOfStatusList();\n      assertThat(statuses)\n              .extracting(Status::getMessage)\n              .contains(\"Found logback-core version 1.5.26\", \"Found logback-classic version 1.5.26\");\n      assertThat(statuses)\n              .filteredOn(status -> status.getLevel() >= Status.WARN)\n              .extracting(Status::getMessage)\n              .doesNotContain(\"Versions of logback-classic and logback-core are different!\");\n    } finally {\n      loggerContext.stop();\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  void legacyJoranReflectionFallbackConfiguresFromClasspathResource() throws Throwable {\n    LoggerContext loggerContext = new LoggerContext();\n    try {\n      ContextInitializer initializer = new ContextInitializer(loggerContext);\n      Configurator.ExecutionStatus status = invokeLegacyJoranReflectionFallback(initializer);\n\n      assertThat(status).isEqualTo(Configurator.ExecutionStatus.DO_NOT_INVOKE_NEXT_IF_ANY);\n      Logger rootLogger = loggerContext.getLogger(Logger.ROOT_LOGGER_NAME);\n      Appender<ILoggingEvent> stdoutAppender = rootLogger.getAppender(\"STDOUT\");\n      assertThat(stdoutAppender).isNotNull();\n      assertThat(stdoutAppender.isStarted()).isTrue();\n    } finally {\n      loggerContext.stop();\n    }\n  }\n\n  private Configurator.ExecutionStatus invokeLegacyJoranReflectionFallback(ContextInitializer initializer)\n          throws Throwable {\n    MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(ContextInitializer.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n    MethodHandle methodHandle = lookup.findVirtual(ContextInitializer.class,\n            \"attemptConfigurationUsingJoranUsingReflexion\",\n            MethodType.methodType(Configurator.ExecutionStatus.class, ClassLoader.class));\n    return (Configurator.ExecutionStatus) methodHandle.invoke(initializer, ContextInitializerTest.class.getClassLoader());\n  }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/src/test/java/org/graalvm/logback/ContextInitializerTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org.graalvm.logback;\\n\\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.Logger;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.Configurator;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.ILoggingEvent;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.classic.util.ContextInitializer;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.core.Appender;\\nimport ch.qos.logback.core.status.Status;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class ContextInitializerTest {\\n\\n  @Test\\n  void autoConfigReportsMatchingSelfDeclaredVersions() throws Exception {\\n    LoggerContext loggerContext = new LoggerContext();\\n    try {\\n      ContextInitializer initializer = new ContextInitializer(loggerContext);\\n      initializer.autoConfig(ContextInitializerTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n\\n      List<Status> statuses = loggerContext.getStatusManager().getCopyOfStatusList();\\n      assertThat(statuses)\\n              .extracting(Status::getMessage)\\n              .contains(\\\"Found logback-core version 1.5.26\\\", \\\"Found logback-classic version 1.5.26\\\");\\n      assertThat(statuses)\\n              .filteredOn(status -> status.getLevel() >= Status.WARN)\\n              .extracting(Status::getMessage)\\n              .doesNotContain(\\\"Versions of logback-classic and logback-core are different!\\\");\\n    } finally {\\n      loggerContext.stop();\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  void legacyJoranReflectionFallbackConfiguresFromClasspathResource() throws Throwable {\\n    LoggerContext loggerContext = new LoggerContext();\\n    try {\\n      ContextInitializer initializer = new ContextInitializer(loggerContext);\\n      Configurator.ExecutionStatus status = invokeLegacyJoranReflectionFallback(initializer);\\n\\n      assertThat(status).isEqualTo(Configurator.ExecutionStatus.DO_NOT_INVOKE_NEXT_IF_ANY);\\n      Logger rootLogger = loggerContext.getLogger(Logger.ROOT_LOGGER_NAME);\\n      Appender<ILoggingEvent> stdoutAppender = rootLogger.getAppender(\\\"STDOUT\\\");\\n      assertThat(stdoutAppender).isNotNull();\\n      assertThat(stdoutAppender.isStarted()).isTrue();\\n    } finally {\\n      loggerContext.stop();\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  private Configurator.ExecutionStatus invokeLegacyJoranReflectionFallback(ContextInitializer initializer)\\n          throws Throwable {\\n    MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(ContextInitializer.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\\n    MethodHandle methodHandle = lookup.findVirtual(ContextInitializer.class,\\n            \\\"attemptConfigurationUsingJoranUsingReflexion\\\",\\n            MethodType.methodType(Configurator.ExecutionStatus.class, ClassLoader.class));\\n    return (Configurator.ExecutionStatus) methodHandle.invoke(initializer, ContextInitializerTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2241, "output": 1319, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37864, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778744179807, "responseId": "resp_0dc4787d6aa6fc64016a057b7494dc81a394e81d2bf5537bc0"}}
